Use daemonSets, haproxy and controller to check SDN connectivity between each nodes in origin.

1. oc create sa sdnchecker

2. oc adm policy add-cluster-role-to-user system:sdn-reader -z sdnchecker

3. edit dc yaml with adding serviceAccount: sdnchecker

4. cat /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token | xargs -I {} curl -k https://172.30.0.1:443/apis/network.openshift.io/v1/hostsubnets -H "Authorization: Bearer {}"

5. oc adm policy add-scc-to-user anyuid -z sdnchecker

6. docker build -t sdnchecker .
